ca.ualberta.cmput301w14t08.geochan.models

Class GeoLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.ualberta.cmput301w14t08.geochan.models.GeoLocation

  • public class GeoLocation
extends Object
    Responsible for GeoLocation services for Comment objects Responsible for keeping track of location, latitude and longitude values, point of interest string (location description), and calculating distance between itself and another geoLocation object.
    Author:
    Brad Simons

      • setCoordinates

        public void setCoordinates(double newLat,
                  double newLong)
        Sets both the longitude and latitude of the GeoLocation to new values. Creates a new location object so that the LocationListenerServices's lastKnownLocation attribute is not affected.
        Parameters:
        newLat - The new latitude to be assigned.
        newLong - The new longitude to be assigned.
